content.detailedDescription: As we were standing in my driveway a starlight object began moving overhead from se to nw. it changed direction and began moving ne. it disappeared. about ten minutes after it disappeared it appeared out of nowhere brighter than it was the first time, following the same flight path in reverse direction. as it got closer to the original sighting location it started to fade and then disappered completely.
content.summary: Star like object moved overhead, disappeared and reappeared.

content.detailedDescription:
A group of my friends (7 of us) were walking on the beach directly in front of the holiday inn highland beach at approx 10:35pm. overhead we saw approaching us in a west to east direction 6 orange disk shaped flying objects. the first two objects we saw we thought were a shooting stars, but the color was wrong and the flying was slower than a shooting star would be. then there was four more of them, for a total of six. they were moving faster them an object would float (like a chinese lantern, which is what we thought secondly) and appeared to be flame lit from the bottom.
they continued to fly into the easterly direction out over the ocean until we could no longer see them. the group felt like we had seen something very strange and all ask each other "did we really just see that?", of course we all had.
content.summary: Six orange colored disk shaped flew over highland beach last night in a west/east direction 10:35pm

content.detailedDescription: My brother in law and i both witnessed a very bright light in the west that was brighter than other stars.  we both assumed at first it was a star but then it began to alternate colors between red, green and blue.  at times the whole object would appear white and then begin changing colors.  we watched the object for nearly an hour.  then it just disappeared.  we did not witness it move.  it was as if someone just turned the lights off and it was suddenly not there.
content.summary: Thought it was a very brigth star at first but it began alternating colors between red, blue and green and it hovered at exactly the same spot for about an hour.  had it been a star it would have appeared to have moved in that span.

content.detailedDescription: Witness sent report to fi, having obtained e-mail address from www.Mufon.Com.
content.summary: Dark craft seen.  later a kc-130 tanker transport flew the exact same path.

content.detailedDescription:
The objects cited above remained staionary for approx 10 minutes in a constellation type pattern.  all the while emitting an amber/orange light
we pulled over to observe, and 6 or 7 objects moved and quickly disappeared.  the remaining object remained stationary for about 3 additional minutes and continued to emit orange/amber light.  it then moved abruptly to my right (south?) and suddenly disappeared.
content.summary: When driving hom at about 10,30 pm june 2 2012 my wife and i observed  6-7 amber/orange lights resembling a constellation formation in a stationary position

content.detailedDescription: I did not see a ufo in the air. i awoke and a shadow caught my attention. at first i thought it was my eyes, i'm 31 and have never been so freaked out in my life. my dog never barked or alerted me. i'm not even sure why i woke up. when i blinked s everal domes and rubbed my eyes i realized i was seeing something. my windows are low so the figure could not have been more than 4ft tall. it was a shadow of a head, larger than a human head and a little skinny neck and shoulders (a bust) that's all i could see. it moved so slowly that, i got the chills. in the other window (we have 5in our master) there was a tall super skinny shadow that slightly made a "y" at the top. as soon as the shadowy figure moved away from the window i hit my husband so hard and (do not to sound completely nuts) i told him someone was outside. he turned on all the lights and grabbed his gun.... :( and ten minutes later, we checked outside and nothing. when we went back to bed i laid there looking for the shadows, but they were both gone. i didn't really go back to sleep and i can't figure out what it was. help please.
content.summary: Not a ufo but a figure.

content.detailedDescription: Saw a giant red orange flame from apartment complex on 43rd floor. i face chicago and have a wraparound window plan in boystown i was visiting my boyfriend who is living in chicago for the summer. were were in park place towers. saw it coming from the right in the distance and head over chicago then to the left to lake michigan. it was very bright. did not fall to earth. just traveled across like a flame but it was red glowing and ornage like. had no trail. but it looked like it was on fire bc it was flickering. it looked to be very large and was moving very fast. its scared the sh*t out of me. was wondering if anyone else say it?
content.summary: On the 43rd floor of apartment complex in boystown in chicago. saw a orange red very large object coming in the direction of the building. coming from the right to the left. the left being lake michigan. was glowing very bright. traveling fast and went

content.detailedDescription: I was outside near my cornfield when i looked up to see two bright white lights moving very slowly to the right. they were shaped like blimps and one was on top of the other with distance apart. they moved behind trees where i could still see them. i was watching the ufo untill it disapeared out of sight. durring the sighting a plane was going by but not near it. it was going the opposite direction. i though the ufo had went behind a building but when i went in front of the building there was nothing in sight but just trees and the moon. it made a faint sound that sounded a little like a plane and a buzzing sound. i did not have any sort of recording device near me at the moment so i had no way of recording the incident. i talked to people around me like neighbors but no one else had seen the two objects. the ufo's were very large compared to the moon that was above them. they were the size of half moons if not larger. i kept searching every night after that to see if i could see the ufo once again but i saw nothing. the first time i saw it i thought they were blimps or planes but they were so close together that i wouldn't be possible. they were also to large to be either. it only moved a little bit, about the speed of slow clouds. the sky was clear and there were no clouds. my mother called me crazy and i was just seeing things. i saw the reflection through my bedroom window and that is why i turned around and looked. i had never seen anything like it and it was so amazing. i never really had believed in such things untill then. i had watched the show fact or faked many times and thought all of it was faked. i was very surprised to realize that none of it was fake. there really or ufo's and aliens.
content.summary: Both were bright white and bigger than blimps. they were shaped like blimps and were moving very slowly to the right.

content.detailedDescription: Was in back yard.  watching night sky while having a cig.  observed bright light in south east sky.. no clouds and alot of stars.  watched as light grew brighter then flashed like a flash bulb and went upward very fast then vanished.  this occurred around 10. pm
